{
  "texts": [
    "Second, despite LLMs' proficiency in generalpurpose information extraction (Xu et al., 2024), they struggle in specialized domains: hallucinating entities, misclassifying relationships, and overlooking tail-domain concepts absent from their training data (Yu et al., 2024).",
    "For example, in climate science, models frequently conflate teleconnections (large-scale climate linkages) with generic correlations or fail to recognize emerging terms like 'Arctic amplification'.",
    "These errors compromise KG reliability for downstream tasks.",
    "A critical bottleneck in KG construction lies in accurate named entity recognition (NER) for specialized domains.",
    "State-of-the-art generalist models like GLiNER (Zaratiana et al., 2024), which achieve competitive performance on broadcoverage benchmarks (F1: 0.478), falter in domainspecific settings-scoring only 0.339 F1 on climate science texts."
  ]
}